<body>
    <button class="fixedExample">Fixed Example</button>

    <div class="container">


        <div class="static">
            <div class="heading">Static Position</div>
            <p>Static position is by default position of html</p>

        </div>

        <hr>

        <div class="relative">
            <div class="heading">Relative Position</div>
            <p>Relative Position is relative to parent tage, where we can adjust the position using top and left</p>
            <p class="relativeExample">This is example of relative position</p>
        </div>

        <hr>

        <div class="fixed">
            <div class="heading">Fixed Position</div>
            <p>Fixed Position is fixed, it would be fixed even if the scrollbar is active</p>



        </div>

        <hr>


        <div class="absolute">
            <div class="heading">Absolute Position</div>
            <p>Absolute position is fixed postion relative to its parents element, if parent element not available then it will be relative to body tag</p>

            <div class="absoluteParent">
                <div class="absoluteExample">
                    ABsolute Example
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <hr>


        <div class="sticky">
            <div class="heading">Sticky Position</div>
            <p>Sticky position is the combination of relative and fixed and based on top and left property it, toggles between </p>
        </div>





    </div>

    <div class="stickyExample">
        Sticky Example
    </div>

